2.Definitions:


Luna is a software product (bot) for the Discord platform, providing functionality to users. The full list of functions is available via the /help command in the Discord interface. Hereinafter referred to as Luna
User - The end user of discord using the service.
Prohibited Content - You are prohibited from posting, distributing, or providing access to Content that is illegal, harmful, threatening, defamatory, invasive of privacy, or that we, in our sole discretion, deem unacceptable. Such Prohibited Content includes, but is not limited to:Sexual Content: Pornography, explicit sexual material, content related to sexual exploitation, and any material depicting minors in a sexualized context.Extremely Violent and Shocking Content: Realistic depictions or descriptions of violence, cruelty, torture, murder, bodily harm, as well as depictions of corpses, dismembered bodies, or other consequences of violent acts in shocking detail.Abuse of People and Animals: Material depicting or promoting physical or psychological bullying, humiliation, torture, infliction of suffering on people or animals.Hate Speech: Materials that promote violence or discrimination against individuals or groups based on race, ethnic origin, religion, disability, gender, age, sexual orientation, or other characteristics.Content Violating Human Rights: Threats of violence, cyberbullying, harassment, invasion of privacy, and dissemination of personal information without consent (doxing).We reserve the right, at our sole discretion, to remove any Content that violates these Terms, and take action against accounts posting such Content, up to and including reporting to Discord for their blocking. Any content that violates Discord's Terms of Service or Discord Community Guidelines is also considered Prohibited Content for the purposes of this Agreement.


3.Rules of Use:
When using Luna, the User is prohibited from performing the following actions:
1- Using the bot's functionality for illegal/Unlawful actions, 2- Using the bot for spam/phishing, etc., Violation of Discord's Terms of Service 3- (https://discord.com/terms),
4- Using the bot to Distribute prohibited content,
5- Any actions aimed at disrupting the bot's operation: DDoS Attacks, exploitation of Vulnerabilities, and other similar actions.


In case of violation of the rules of use, the Owner has the right to suspend or completely terminate access to the Service for a specific User or an entire server (guild) at its sole discretion, without mandatory prior notice.


The services of the service may only be used by users who have reached the age corresponding to the minimum age for using the Discord platform.


4.Service Services:
The service is provided "as is", without warranties. The Developer is not responsible for direct or indirect losses such as: loss of data within the bot (Data in databases, etc.), Cessation of the bot's operation, loss of statistics, Or for losses resulting from the actions of the user or third parties. The Developer also does not guarantee uninterrupted operation of the service and/or that it will meet expectations.


5.Data Collection and Use:
Luna has the right to collect user data to provide functionality, such as: User IDs, Server IDs, message IDs. User or server avatars. User nicknames as well as other data necessary for the functioning of specific commands and features of the bot. For more details, see the Privacy Policy


6.Terms of Changes to the Terms of Use (ToU):
The Project Owner reserves the right to change the terms without notifying the user. The updated version comes into force from the moment of publication. Continued use of the bot after the changes take effect signifies agreement with them.


